<subSubSection id="EECE063D326BAC69A00E4A663949DB20" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D11C9F3CB6FC07A157B32AF2E3F64060" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2CF300078E99C5268EFFE4A78618DE3" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Differs from other members of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="454360ADC370A1AE407D9E0F1D81A0E8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="(Tetrardisia)" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Tetrardisia">Tetrardisia</taxonomicName>
in having linear-oblong leaves, with a long, acuminate-caudate apex, and finely serrulate margins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
